snippet: The private-equity consortium that is struggling to complete a takeover of Qantas Airways said that its bid would not be extended beyond May 4.
lead_paragraph: SYDNEY, Australia, April 22 (Dow Jones) — The private-equity consortium that is struggling to complete a takeover of Qantas Airways in Australia said Sunday that its bid would not be extended beyond May 4.

headline.main: No Extension for Qantas, Bidders Say
headline.print_headline: No Extension For Qantas, Bidders Say

abstract: Southern California is starting to muscle out New England for second place behind Silicon Valley as a magnet for venture capital. A report scheduled to be released Monday by the research and consulting firms Ernst & Young and Dow Jones VentureOne underscores Southern California’s attractiveness, especially to financiers of the healthcare and biotechnology industries in San Diego County and information technology firms in Los Angeles.
